      • isTouch

        public boolean isTouch()
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyNotification
        Returns true if this notification represents an event that did not change the state of the notifying object. For the events IPropertyNotification.ADD, IPropertyNotification.ADD_MANY, IPropertyNotification.REMOVE, IPropertyNotification.REMOVE_MANY, IPropertyNotification.MOVE, it always returns false. For the events IPropertyNotification.RESOLVE and IPropertyNotification.REMOVING_ADAPTER it always returns true. For the events IPropertyNotification.SET and IPropertyNotification.UNSET it returns true if the old and the new value are equal; In addition, for certain types of features there may be a distinction between being set to a default value and not being set at all, which implies that it has the default value. In this situation, even in the case that the old and new values are equal, isTouch may never the less return false in order to indicate that, although the value has not changed, the feature has gone from simply having a default value to being set to that same default value, or has gone from being set to the default value back to being unset.
        Specified by:
        isTouch in interface IPropertyNotification
        Returns:
        whether or not this is a state changing modification.
